                  <summary>Upside down small script from one of the two pieces may have been an account, "six dirhams" below which, "dirham and a third"; the other side of two, that with only one text, large script on one piece, very small on other.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">May have had an actual text, but clearly one sheet is the mirror image of the other, i.e., the writing has seeped from one to the other.</note>
